HEADWORD: Revolvency
<hw>Re*volv"en*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or state
of revolving; revolution.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Its own <qex>revolvency</qex> upholds the world.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revolver</ent>⟦br⟧
